&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;IntelliDyne is looking for a hands-on technical manager capable of leading a highly talented team on daily IT operations and project progress&amp;nbsp;while&amp;nbsp;developing solutions&amp;nbsp;and leading development teams&amp;nbsp;that exceed customer expectations. &amp;nbsp;The&amp;nbsp;Project Manager possesses&amp;nbsp;SharePoint&amp;nbsp;skills and is&amp;nbsp;responsible for managing the Division&#39;s Information Technology (IT) and IT Security Program. This objective is to provide a wide range of IT business solutions to its customers, providing secure, reliable, and highly available IT business solutions to fulfill program requirements, serving a few thousand end-users located within the Washington, DC area.  The Project Manager will provide effective enterprise-level support and services which provide the Government&amp;nbsp;customer with&amp;nbsp;the resources needed to achieve its operational objectives.  The qualified candidate must be capable of performing management duties that cover the scope of this job description whenever needed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;The SharePoint&amp;nbsp;Project Manager&amp;nbsp;will assist the Government client in the requirements, analysis, design, development, deployment, and maintenance of Enterprise SharePoint projects. The&amp;nbsp;Project&amp;nbsp;Manager&amp;nbsp;will be the&amp;nbsp;primary point of contact for the SharePoint&amp;nbsp;team&amp;nbsp;and serve as subject matter expert.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
